                            <comment id="17514024" author="tibor17" created="Tue, 29 Mar 2022 11:30:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://gitbox.apache.org/repos/asf?p=maven-surefire.git;a=commit;h=32f7dd36208abe059f6cfb01e79571b03c158806&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://gitbox.apache.org/repos/asf?p=maven-surefire.git;a=commit;h=32f7dd36208abe059f6cfb01e79571b03c158806&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17713763" author="stevel@apache.org" created="Tue, 18 Apr 2023 20:32:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;why? this removes the ability to get detailed results from test failures if you have complex tests without editing every pom file.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I really consider this a regression&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17714051" author="jglick@netbeans.org" created="Wed, 19 Apr 2023 10:58:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=stevel%40apache.org&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;stevel@apache.org&quot;&gt;stevel@apache.org&lt;/a&gt; how would defaulting &lt;tt&gt;trimStackTrace&lt;/tt&gt; to &lt;tt&gt;false&lt;/tt&gt; &lt;em&gt;remove&lt;/em&gt; the ability to the get detailed results from test failures? In certain cases (depending on the sort of application) it &lt;em&gt;restores&lt;/em&gt; that ability. Setting it to &lt;tt&gt;true&lt;/tt&gt; is fine if you know from experience that in your application domain, test framework, etc. the trimmed lines will in fact be irrelevant, and you want to make the root cause easier to spot instantly without distractions.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17714090" author="stevel@apache.org" created="Wed, 19 Apr 2023 12:51:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think the issue is to restore the current behaviour we have to alter all our existing build files&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
